title: Investors ‘Un-Like’ Facebook (FB) As Stock Price Languishes
text: After falling nearly 13 percent during the September swoon, the Nasdaq Composite has rallied back to within 5 percent of its all-time highs in October. Meanwhile, a few notorious tech stocks are not rallying with the same strength.

title: Liz Ann Sonders on FAANG stocks: There is antitrust risk regardless of election results
text: Liz Ann Sonders, Charles Schwab chief investment strategist, joins 'Closing Bell' to talk about how she's telling investors to be mindful of pairing big tech stocks as the crackdown on antitrust continues.

title: Step Up Or Break Up: The Challenge For Big Tech
text: Evidence suggests the Big Five maintain their dominance thanks to insufficient regulation, anticompetitive behavior & business models that manipulate users. The risks they pose to civic society are immense however they can still become stewards of the societies that have powered their success.

title: Facebook Stock Shrugs Off House Report Calling It a Monopoly
text: Facebook was accused of having monopolistic power by the House Antitrust Subcommittee, but Facebook stock was unfazed. The post Facebook Stock Shrugs Off House Report Calling It a Monopoly appeared first on InvestorPlace.

title: Factbox: Big Tech's market dominance spurs numerous U.S. antitrust probes
text: The four Big Tech companies -- Alphabet's Google , Amazon , Apple and Facebook -- face an array of antitrust investigations at the federal and state level which were revealed in mid-2019.

title: Facebook’s China Tactics Backfire
text: Facebook complaining about a bad policy that the company helped initiate is more than an eye-rolling joke.

title: Facebook's former chief privacy officer on decision to halt post-election ads
text: Chris Kelly, former Facebook chief privacy officer, joins "Squawk Alley" to discuss Facebook's decision to halt political ads after the election.

title: Insider CEO Henry Blodget on how Microsoft's antitrust history compares to today
text: Big Tech regulation is back in focus this week after a House committee called some big names monopolies. Henry Blodget, CEO and co-founder of Insider, joins "Squawk Box" to discuss.

title: Should Tech Investors Worry About Antitrust?
text: Investors should take a deep breath before panic-selling.
